== Equipment Overview ==
* '''Station:''' Pace ADS200 with AccuDrive temperature control technology — closed-loop, load-sensing power delivery up to 120W
* '''Iron:''' TD-200 tip-heater cartridge iron with aluminum Cool Touch handle
* '''Tip-to-grip distance:''' 1.9" (48 mm) — short for precision work under magnification
* '''Temperature stability:''' +/-1.1C (2F) at idle
* '''Tip-to-ground resistance:''' Less than 2 ohms (meets ANSI/J-STD-001)
* '''Tip system:''' Blue Series tip-heater cartridges — integrated sensor and heater in each cartridge, no separate calibration needed per tip

== Tip Cartridges ==
The ADS200 uses Blue Series tip-heater cartridges. Each cartridge contains its own heater and temperature sensor, so swapping tips does not require recalibration.

Common cartridges to keep on hand:
{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Cartridge !! Tip Shape !! Use Case
|-
| 1131-0053 || Chisel 1/16" (1.6 mm) || General through-hole and SMD
|-
| 1131-0054 || Chisel 3/32" (2.4 mm) || Larger pads, connectors, ground planes
|-
| 1131-0050 || Conical 0.4 mm || Fine-pitch SMD, tight spaces
